@page "/accessibility"
@using UI.Services
@inject IAccessibilitySettingService SettingService

<div class="vertical-stack aic mb20">
	<FluentCard Class="common-card-style">
		<div class="card-header">
			<h4>Checkboxes vs. Sliders</h4>
		</div>
		<div class="vertical-stack card-body">
			<p>Action dots and experience trackers on the character sheet pages are implemented with a row of checkboxes by default. This makes linguistic sense because the language used is frequently to "mark a point" of something.</p>
			<p>However, some users may find a slider component easier to use with keyboard navigation and less repetitive while using screen readers.</p>
			<FluentSwitch Label="Desired Component" Value="UseSlider" ValueChanged="RatingSwitchValueChanged">
				<span slot="checked-message">Slider</span>
				<span slot="unchecked-message">Checkboxes</span>
			</FluentSwitch>
			<div style="max-width: 165px;">
				<BladeRating MaxValue="6" CheckboxAriaLabelSuffix="Testable" Value="RatingSwitchValue" />
			</div>
		</div>
	</FluentCard>
</div>
